  "description": "Nils Rikard Molin was a Swedish first librarian, born on February 7, 1892, in Gothenburg. He was the son of builder Janne M. and Albertina Svensson. He married Anna Röding, a doctor of philosophy, on March 31, 19--. They had two children: Björn, born in 1932, and Tan, born in 1934. Molin completed his Bachelor of Arts degree in 1917, Licentiate in Philosophy in 1924, and Doctorate in Philosophy in 1931, all at Gothenburg University. He started his career as a deputy assistant librarian at Gothenburg City Library in 1918 and progressed to become an assistant librarian in 1920, second librarian in 1930, and first librarian in 1940. From 1930 to 1932, Molin served as a librarian for the Western Swedish Educational Association. He contributed to various publications, including translations by Karl August Hagberg, dissertations on Shakespeare, and revised editions of K.A. Hagberg's translations of Shakespeare's dramatic works."
